{{main|无主土地|失竊的一代}}
澳大利亞日的慶祝備受部份[[澳洲人|澳洲人]]的爭議，尤其是對[[澳大利亞原住民|澳大利亞原住民]]來說，這天代表他們的土地被[[白人|白人]]入侵，亦是往後兩百多年來所受到的非人道對待（例如「[[失竊的一代|失竊的一代]]事件」等等）的開端<ref>[http://hk.apple.nextmedia.com/realtime/art_main.php?&iss_id=20120127&sec_id=10793140&art_id=50062006 澳總理避抗議甩鞋土著放上網拍賣《蘋果日報》2012年1月27日]</ref>。

一些澳大利亞人認為澳大利亞日是[[大英帝國|英國]]殖民者的定居日，是殖民者對澳大利亞土著帶來不利影響的象徵<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/stories/2009/01/26/2474568.htm |title=Invasion day protests amid Australia Day debate |date=2009-01-26 |accessdate=2010-10-15 |language=en |archive-date=2011-05-11 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110511141922/http://www.abc.net.au/news/stories/2009/01/26/2474568.htm |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.smh.com.au/national/obey-the-law-at-least-abbott-tells-migrants-20100122-mqox.html | work=The Sydney Morning Herald | title=Obey the law at least, Abbott tells migrants | first=Yuko | last=Narushima | date=2010-01-23 | language=en | accessdate=2019-01-26 | archive-date=2021-04-20 | archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210420173906/https://www.smh.com.au/national/obey-the-law-at-least-abbott-tells-migrants-20100122-mqox.html | dead-url=no }}</ref>。1938年，有原住民在此澳洲日慶祝活動上哀悼。1988年，在悉尼的原住民舉行了大型“入侵日”紀念活動，紀念土著文化的喪失<ref name=Age09>{{cite news|url=http://www.theage.com.au/national/90-years-apart-and-bonded-by-a-nation-20090124-7p4i.html|title=90 years apart and bonded by a nation|accessdate=2009-01-25|language=en|last=Tippet|first=Gary|date=2009-01-25|publisher=Australia Day Council of New South Wales | location=Melbourne| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20090131062523/http://www.theage.com.au/national/90-years-apart-and-bonded-by-a-nation-20090124-7p4i.html| archivedate= 2009-01-31 | deadurl= no}}</ref>。一些土著和其他人將澳大利亞日稱為“入侵日”，抗議活動幾乎每年都會發生，有時是在澳大利亞日活動<ref name="AgeRecon">{{cite news|url=http://www.theage.com.au/news/opinion/reconciliation-can-start-on-australia-day/2007/01/28/1169919208491.html|title=Reconciliation can start on Australia Day|date=2007-01-29|work=[[世紀報|世紀報]]|location=Melbourne, Australia|accessdate=2008-12-18|language=en|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090113182224/http://www.theage.com.au/news/opinion/reconciliation-can-start-on-australia-day/2007/01/28/1169919208491.html|archivedate=2009-01-13|deadurl=no}}</ref>，成千上萬的人參加首都城市的抗議遊行<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.abc.net.au/news/2018-01-26/invasion-day-protests-in-melbourne-and-sydney/9364940|title=Invasion Day marked by thousands of protesters calling for equal rights, change of date|website=[[ABC新聞24|ABC新聞24]]|date=2018-01-27|accessdate=2018-01-30|language=en|archive-date=2020-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109042514/https://www.abc.net.au/news/2018-01-26/invasion-day-protests-in-melbourne-and-sydney/9364940|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.heraldsun.com.au/news/victoria/australia-day-2018-heavy-police-presence-around-melbourne-rallies/news-story/3cd02836c7e636edd2219b86bab3bb3d|title=Australia Day 2018: Thousands turn out for protest in Melbourne CBD|work={{link-en|太陽先驅報|Herald Sun}}|date=2018-01-26|access-date=2018-01-28|language=en|archive-date=2021-01-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210107075014/https://www.heraldsun.com.au/news/victoria/australia-day-2018-heavy-police-presence-around-melbourne-rallies/news-story/3cd02836c7e636edd2219b86bab3bb3d|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2018/jan/26/abolish-australia-day-invasion-day-marches-draw-tens-of-thousands-of-protesters|last1=Knaus|first1=Christopher|last2=Wahlquist|first2=Calla|title='Abolish Australia Day': Invasion Day marches draw tens of thousands of protesters|work=[[衛報|衛報]]|date=2018-01-26|accessdate=2018-01-27|language=en|archive-date=2020-11-09|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201109011120/https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2018/jan/26/abolish-australia-day-invasion-day-marches-draw-tens-of-thousands-of-protesters|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2019/jan/25/invasion-day-rally-2019-where-to-find-marches-and-protests-across-australia|title=Invasion Day rally 2019: where to find marches and protests across Australia|work=衛報|date=2019-01-25|accessdate=2019-01-25|language=en|archive-date=2020-12-02|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201202191525/https://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2019/jan/25/invasion-day-rally-2019-where-to-find-marches-and-protests-across-australia|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

澳洲日也被稱為「生存日」，並以1992年首次在悉尼舉行的生存日音樂會等活動為標誌。儘管殖民標誌和歧視仍然存在，「生存日」慶祝土著人民和文化得以留存<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.cityofsydney.nsw.gov.au/barani/themes/theme6.htm|title= Significant Aboriginal Events in Sydney|accessdate=2007-01-29|language=en|work=[[雪梨市|雪梨市]]議會官網| archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20070204133848/http://www.cityofsydney.nsw.gov.au/barani/themes/theme6.htm| archivedate= 2007-02-04 | deadurl= no}}</ref>。2016年，澳洲{{link-ja|國家原住民電視台|National Indigenous Television}}選擇“
「生存日」作為首標題，因為它承認澳洲日的混合性質<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sbs.com.au/nitv/explainer/australia-day-invasion-day-survival-day-whats-name|title=Australia Day, Invasion Day, Survival Day: What's in a name?|publisher=|language=en|access-date=2019-01-26|archive-date=2021-04-20|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210420173955/https://www.sbs.com.au/nitv/explainer/australia-day-invasion-day-survival-day-whats-name|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

隨後，官方慶祝活動時試圖與土著人民一起舉行儀式。如在悉尼舉行的Woggan-ma-gule儀式，這個儀式紀念了澳洲的歷史並慶祝當下<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.smh.com.au/news/national/young-and-free-gather-to-rejoice/2008/01/26/1201157739742.html|title=Young and free gather to rejoice – National – smh.com.au|website=www.smh.com.au|access-date=2017-01-13|language=en|archive-date=2017-08-24|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170824174355/http://www.smh.com.au/news/national/young-and-free-gather-to-rejoice/2008/01/26/1201157739742.html|dead-url=no}}</ref>。

